Example
Set the text in the status bar:

Copy
window.status = "Some text in the status bar!!";

Description
The status property sets the text in the status bar at the bottom of the browser, or returns the previously set text.

The defaultStatus property specifies the default text displayed in the status bar.

To allow scripts to change the text of the status, the user must set the dom.disable_window_status_change preference to false in the about:config screen.

In Firefox: "Tools > Options > Content -Enable JavaScript / Advanced > Allow scripts to change status bar text".

Syntax
Copy
window.status
Return Value
A String, representing the text displayed in the status bar
